# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:7
translate spanish counselorconversation5_0c2aa4f4:

    # pc "I kind of miss Brazil."
    pc "Echo un poco de menos Brasil."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:8
translate spanish counselorconversation5_2ec566c7:

    # sc "I bet. Was it nice there?"
    sc "Me lo imagino. ¿Estaba bien allí?"

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:9
translate spanish counselorconversation5_ef088408:

    # pc "It was, most of the time."
    pc "Sí, la mayor parte del tiempo."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:10
translate spanish counselorconversation5_ffefa487:

    # sc "Most of the time?"
    sc "¿La mayor parte del tiempo?"

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:11
translate spanish counselorconversation5_f6155a33:

    # pc "Well the places that I stayed at were very nice."
    pc "Bueno, los sitios en los que me alojé eran muy bonitos."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:12
translate spanish counselorconversation5_444ece6f:

    # pc "But Brazil has a sort of split-personality."
    pc "Pero Brasil tiene una especie de doble personalidad."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:13
translate spanish counselorconversation5_9247b82f:

    # pc "It's absolutely beautiful in most of the places that I stayed."
    pc "Es absolutamente precioso en la mayoría de los sitios en los que me alojé."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:14
translate spanish counselorconversation5_6ce76dfd:

    # pc "But occasionally, I saw the other side, where people were so poor and hungry and had no way to better themselves."
    pc "Pero, de vez en cuando, veía la otra cara, donde la gente era muy pobre y pasaba hambre, y no tenía forma de mejorar su situación."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:15
translate spanish counselorconversation5_64352ea1:

    # sc "That must have been eye-opening."
    sc "Eso debió de ser revelador."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:16
translate spanish counselorconversation5_ad0a9fab:

    # pc "It was. I know that people are like that in places,"
    pc "Lo fue. Sé que hay gente así en algunos sitios,"

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:17
translate spanish counselorconversation5_b47c5612:

    # pc "But it was so strange to see all of that, then go back to the dorm where I was living and nobody seemed to care."
    pc "pero era muy extraño ver todo eso y luego volver a la residencia donde vivía y que a nadie pareciera importarle."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:18
translate spanish counselorconversation5_ba9df9c6:

    # sc "We tend to ignore the nasty things in life that don't affect us personally."
    sc "Tendemos a ignorar las cosas desagradables de la vida que no nos afectan personalmente."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:19
translate spanish counselorconversation5_34e34dc1:

    # sc "It's a sort of coping mechanism. If we were constantly worried about every bad thing happening, we'd probably have a stroke."
    sc "Es una especie de mecanismo de defensa. Si estuviéramos constantemente preocupados por todo lo malo que ocurre, probablemente nos daría un infarto."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:20
translate spanish counselorconversation5_e46768d7:

    # pc "I guess so, it's just hard to put some of that stuff out of my mind."
    pc "Supongo que sí, pero me cuesta mucho sacarme algunas de esas cosas de la cabeza."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:21
translate spanish counselorconversation5_2426cfe6:

    # sc "You shouldn't. You should keep it there. It will make you a better person."
    sc "No deberías. Deberías mantenerlo ahí. Te convertirá en una mejor persona."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:22
translate spanish counselorconversation5_4a449be8:

    # sc "Know that these things are happening, and know that you are privileged to have the life that you have."
    sc "Sé consciente de que estas cosas están pasando, y sé consciente de que tienes el privilegio de tener la vida que tienes."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:23
translate spanish counselorconversation5_e88d7ffc:

    # pc "You're right."
    pc "Tienes razón."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:25
translate spanish counselorconversation5_067380d2:

    # sc "You have a good heart. Have you seen The Breakfast Club?"
    sc "Tienes buen corazón. ¿Has visto El club de los cinco?"

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:28
translate spanish counselorconversation5_a6773fcb:

    # pc "Sure. Everybody has seen that, right?"
    pc "Claro. Todo el mundo la ha visto, ¿no?"

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:30
translate spanish counselorconversation5_8c93b784:

    # pc "I haven't seen it."
    pc "Yo no la he visto."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:31
translate spanish counselorconversation5_14e2d7b8:

    # sc "Well there's a line in it that Ally Sheedy says."
    sc "Bueno, hay una frase que dice Ally Sheedy."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:32
translate spanish counselorconversation5_314554fe:

    # sc "She says, \"When you grow up, your heart dies.\""
    sc "Dice: «Cuando creces, tu corazón muere»."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:33
translate spanish counselorconversation5_67060d07:

    # sc "And it's true for a lot of people. As they grow up, they become jaded and cynical and stop caring about things."
    sc "Y es cierto para mucha gente. A medida que crecen, se vuelven hastiados y cínicos y dejan de preocuparse por las cosas."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:34
translate spanish counselorconversation5_9123a037:

    # sc "But you're still young. You have a good heart. Don't let it die, okay?"
    sc "Pero tú aún eres joven. Tienes un buen corazón. No dejes que muera, ¿vale?"

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:35
translate spanish counselorconversation5_dd9a629d:

    # pc "I won't."
    pc "No lo haré."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:37
translate spanish counselorconversation5_37653c95:

    # sc "Okay, well you better get to class."
    sc "Vale, pues mejor que vayas a clase."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:38
translate spanish counselorconversation5_a8c43555:

    # pc "Okay, I'll see you next time Gertrude."
    pc "Vale, nos vemos la próxima vez, Gertrude."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:39
translate spanish counselorconversation5_1b784c07:

    # sc "Bye, [pcname]."
    sc "Adiós, [pcname]."

# game/Scenes/CounselorChats/Conversations/5 - Brazil.rpy:40
translate spanish counselorconversation5_e4b88e88:

    # "With that, I stand up and head to class."
    "Con eso, me levanto y me dirijo a clase."

